        <tr><td><font face="Tolk, Times, serif" class="h1font"><font color="#8989B1">Intermediate Decks</font></B></font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td width="2"></td><td valign="top"> 
      <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="5"><tr><td><font face="  Times, Times New Roman, serif" class="bfont"><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0"><tr><td colspan="2"><font face="Tolk, Times, serif" class="h1font">Azzkickin&#8217; Rangers & Burdening Nazgûl</font></td></tr><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Papy, Times, serif" class="h2font"> Rating</Font></TD><TD><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size=1>(4.70)</font> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=21283">Read Reviews</A></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Papy, Times, serif" class="h2font"> Author</font></TD><TD><font face="  Times, Times New Roman, serif" class="bfont"> <A HREF="http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=9318">Stefan "Crom Cruaich" Baas</A></FONT> <font face="Papy, Times, serif" class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=9318&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a></font></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Papy, Times, serif" class="h2font"> Description</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="  Times, Times New Roman, serif" class="bfont"> A tight, powerfull Ranger fellowship combined with Nazgûl-that-add-burdens.</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Papy, Times, serif" class="h2font"> Submitted</Font></TD><TD><font face="  Times, Times New Roman, serif" class="bfont"> February 8, 2002</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Papy, Times, serif" class="h2font"> Cards</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="  Times, Times New Roman, serif" class="bfont"> Starting:<br>
Frodo, Old Bilbo&#8217;s Heir<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(182)">The One Ring, The Ruling Ring</a><br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(245)">Aragorn, King in Exile</a><br>
<br>
Adventure:<br>
1: <a href="javascript:card_browser(206)">Westfarthing</a><br>
2: <a href="javascript:card_browser(208)">Bree Streets</a><br>
3: <a href="javascript:card_browser(879)">Ford of Bruinen</a><br>
4: <a href="javascript:card_browser(225)">Moria Lake</a><br>
5: The Bridge<br>
6: <a href="javascript:card_browser(881)">Lothlórien Woods</a><br>
7: <a href="javascript:card_browser(233)">Anduin Wilderland</a><br>
8: Shores of Nen Nithoel<br>
9: <a href="javascript:card_browser(242)">Summit of Amon Hen</a><br>
<br>
Free Peoples (35):<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(245)">Aragorn, King in Exile</a> (starting)<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(306)">Boromir, Lord of Gondor</a> x2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(191)">Arwen, Daughter of Elrond</a> x2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(164)">Thrarin, Dwarven Smith</a><br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(170)">Bounder</a><br>
A Ranger&#8217;s Versatility x3<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(15)">Swordsman of the Northern Kingdom</a> x4<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(8)">No Stranger to the Shadows</a> x4<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(852)">The Saga of Elendil</a><br>
Aragorn&#8217;s Bow<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(303)">Armor</a> x2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(304)">Athelas</a> x3<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(305)">Blade of Gondor</a><br>
Ranger&#8217;s Sword x2<br>
<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(247)">Defiance</a> x2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(251)">Elven Bow</a><br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(256)">Gwemegil</a><br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(274)">The Tale of Gil-galad</a><br>
<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(190)">Power According to His Stature</a><br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(194)">Sting</a><br>
<br>
Shadow (35):<br>
The Witchking x2<br>
Ulaire Attëa x2<br>
Ulaire Cantëa<br>
Ulaire Enquëa x3<br>
Ulaire Lemenya x2<br>
Ulaire Nelya x2<br>
Ulaire Toldëa x3<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(146)">Morgul Skulker</a> x4<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(100)">All Blades Perish</a> x2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(106)">Dark Whispers</a> x2<br>
In the Ringwraith&#8217;s Wake x2<br>
Return to it&#8217;s Master<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(112)">Morgul Gates</a> x2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(89)">Relentless</a> Charge x2<br>
Nazgûl Sword x3<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(163)">Thin and Stretched</a> x2<br>
    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Papy, Times, serif" class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="  Times, Times New Roman, serif" class="bfont"> <br>
Shadow:<br>
This Shadow deck is not aimed on corrupting the Ring-bearer, but simply to add some usefull burdens. As you all know; Nazgûl work well with burdens, they only have trouble adding them (they only have Drawn to It&#8217;s Power and The Twilight World). This deck solves that. Morgul Skulkers are very common in a Ringwraith-deck, because they can get valuable cards back into your deck. In this deck they have another purpose; to exert them for Thin and Stretched.<br>
Once this card is on the table, Burdens should be adding up in a steady rate. Mostly because no-one would want their Ring-Bearer to skirmish a Nazgûl. If they do dare to put up a fight with Frodo, play Return to It&#8217;s Master. This card is also really useful if they try to be smart and assign a Morgul Skulker to Frodo. It&#8217;s 7 Strength is hardly a real &#8216;overwhelming&#8217; treat to Frodo&#8230; but then comes Return to It&#8217;s Master in play. Always fun to assign him to the Witchking or Attëa. <br>
My favorite: All Blades Perish. Did your opponent think he could kill an exhausted Witchking with Frodo, playing PATHS? I don&#8217;t think so! That  burden he just added would only help me!<br>
<br>
Fellowship:<br>
I usually play with four companions. This to prevent Uruk-Hai decks from getting to dangerous (Uruk-Hai is quite common where I play). All companions (except Frodo) are Rangers and have the Aragorn Signet, enabling them to get healed by KIE. Get &#8216;No Stranger to The Shadows&#8217; on them ASAP. Three Rangers travelling for free can be quite a pain for your opponent; denying them three Twilight every turn. Furthermore the Strategy is quite obvious: ARV the big, nasty critters, use Aragorn&#8217;s Bow to take them out. Let Boromir/ Arwen do the heavy fighting; heal them with KIE. Use Thrarin as cannonfodder. Exert Frodo for Sting to take Twilight away, etc. <br>
<br>
Sites<br>
1: WestFarthing: No PP. When you go first, deny your opponent to draw Aragorn. This site enables you to exert Frodo to deny your opponent one Twilight. You should see his face when he only misses one token to play his shadow-thing.<br>
2: Bree Streets: IMHO this is the best Nazgûl Site 2. I can mostly get 2 Nazgûl out here. Especially if the play Aragorn at their PP (costs 4), have already three companions (Frodo + 2 Starting). Thus making the move-cost 4, plus 1 from the site, plus any Fellowship actions they played. This gives you about 9-12 Twilight to work with. Minus any Roaming cost there would have been. <br>
3: Ford of Bruinen: Nazgûl heaven; witchking for 3, Attëa for 1. Only drawback; it is a river. Which makes it a perfect target for ARV.<br>
4: Moria Lake; With Frodo exerted, they can exert one time less for my In the Ringwraith&#8217;s Wake or Sting.<br>
5: The Bridge of Khazad-Dûm; SURPISE THEM! They never see this coming!<br>
6: LothLorien Woods: A save haven for my Rangers. Nice forest for my ARV<br>
7: Anduin Wilderland: If my opponent gets ahead of me he will have to deal with this site. This site is a killer! Makes his ARV much less effective if he can&#8217;t shoot them down.<br>
8: Shores of Nen Nithoel: I like it&#8217;s high Twilight. It gives you 3 (!!!) more twilight then the other sites 8. <br>
9: Summit of Amon Hen: My favorite site of all: If my burdening strat worked, you can get a lot of  additional cards here. I have killed a lot of opponents with this site.<br>
<br>
This is it! Please criticize me. But be mild, &#8216;cause this is the first deck I have ever posted here.<br>
 </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font face="  Times, Times New Roman, serif" class="bfont"> <a href="/lotr/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=21283"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=21283" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font face="Papy, Times, serif" class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/lotr/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></font></td></tr></table></td></tr></table> <!-- #EndEditable --></td>
